<section xml:id="sec-2-4-Exponential_Growth_and_Geometric_Sequences" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
    <title>Exponential Growth and Geometric Sequences</title>
    <p><em>Exponential Growth and Geometric Sequences</em> discusses the recursion of 
        repeated multiplication to arrive at an arithmetic sequence. The explicit 
        formula is also discussed, including its connection to the recursive formula and 
        to the standard exponential growth model used in Continuously
        <xref ref="sec-6-4-Compounding_Interest" text="title"/> and
        <xref ref="sec-6-5-Radioactive_Decay" text="title"/> , among other lessons. 
        We prefer sequences to begin with the term  
        <m>g_0</m> rather than  <m>g_1</m>. Therefore, the explicit formula is given as  
        <m>g_n = g_0 r^n</m> rather than <m>g_n = g_1 r^{n - 1}</m> .</p>
        
